

## Task 4: Billing System Implementation

**Implementation Guide:** [Stripe Integration Guide](https://www.notion.so/Stripe-Integration-Guide-Solar-Energy-Billing-2bea93edaaa7803f88fad366b9edd9f6?pvs=21)

### Business Context

The company charges users for the energy their solar units generate. Every month, based on the solar unit's installation date, users receive an invoice outlining their energy generation for the billing period. Users can view and pay these invoices through the dashboard via Stripe.

### 4.1 Backend Requirements

**Invoice Generation:**

- ✅ Automatically generate monthly invoices for each solar unit
- ✅ Billing cycle anchored to the unit's installation date
- ✅ Calculate total energy generated (kWh) for the billing period
- ✅ New invoices start with PENDING status

**Invoice Management:**

- ✅ Users can retrieve their own invoices
- ✅ Admins can view all invoices across users
- ✅ Support filtering by payment status (Pending, Paid, Failed)

**Payment Processing:**

- ✅ Integrate Stripe for payment processing
- ✅ Configure pricing in Stripe Dashboard (per kWh rate)
- ✅ Handle payment webhooks to update invoice status

### 4.2 Frontend Requirements

**User Dashboard:**

- ✅ Invoices page showing all user invoices
- ✅ Filter invoices by status (All, Pending, Paid)
- ✅ View invoice details (billing period, energy generated, amount)
- ✅ Pay pending invoices via Stripe Embedded Checkout
- ✅ Payment confirmation page

**Admin Dashboard:**

- ✅ View all invoices across all users
- ✅ Filter by payment status
- ✅ See which invoices are overdue/unpaid

**Navigation:**

- ✅ Add "Invoices" link to sidebar with pending count badge

